<br>
Though, with the pursuit of wizardly talents, I am at a loss for which skill to pursue.  Tailoring could wield some nice armor at high levels, though farming for silks and such can be such a bore (nevermind the fact you tend to ruin a perfectly good hide with nukes, /sigh).<br>
<br>
Brewing can make some nice tea at higher levels, but obtaining the tea leaves as a dark elf is difficult at best.<br>
<br>
Baking also has it's advantages, though the best recipies require items from that dirty halfling hovel, Rivervale.<br>
<br>
Blacksmithing... /em lifts hammer with her weak Tier'Dal arms, and laughs before dropping it.<br>
<br>
This leaves pottery.  I know that the best items to be made here (sub-PoP recipies) are easily outdone by drops from many mobs, but the ones that do exist (crucible of escape, golden idol of Solusek Ro) are decent items to have for yourself.<br>
<br>
Keep in mind that while I am a twink, my resources do not come from an end-game guild, and I myself will likely never attain greater than passing the tests for valor.  VT, even Skyshrine are but distant dreams.<br>
<br>
What are your thoughts and insights (aside from GM them all, and yes I will be advancing them all a bit for the Shawl Quests)? <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=587299" target="top">Seuinye Whitewater</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> 31 Wizard, Innoruuk</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jakartatorv>JakartaTorv</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 86<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/24/03 2:12:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26254.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.blizzard.com/war3x/images/units/bloodelfsorc.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tradeskills</span><hr size=1> If you have PoP, almost all supplies for any tradeskill can be found in PoK. I've done all my tradeskilling in this zone + SH for a few misc. things, getting PoP will make your tradeskills alot easier   <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=223351" target="top">Sage Jakarta Pastythug</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
