<br>
Currently, I'm 158 tailor, 199 brewing, 196 jewelry, 186 baking, 121 smithing and 148 pottery.<br>
<br>
My plan is to get all of my skills up but it's difficult as a wizzy.  Most of the high end things take foraged items at one point or another and that's something that as a Euridite wizzy I just can't do.  I hate buying things because I'm a poor wizzy but I do ask my hubby to forage for me once in a while.<br>
<br>
The problem with jewelry is that wizzies can't enchant the metal so you have to have a friend do it.<br>
<br>
Tailoring seems to be a good thing to do because we can generally get what we need to do that.<br>
<br>
Brewing and baking take foraged items although I have managed to get brewing up pretty well without too many foraged things.  I make the demi-sec champagne's and for two stacks of those it costs me about 1k pp and my skill has gone from 180 to 199.  (The champagnes are also what got my jewelry skill up.)<br>
<br>
Pottery can be REAL expensive to master.  My brother is a master potterer.  He doesn't skill up as fast as I do in tradeskills.  It's possible that by having a really high int (and knowing that's our main stat) that we skill faster.  He's a paladin and has a decent wisdom but he's not maxed in any of his stats.  He says that it can cost 1k pp for 3 tries at the stage he's at.  He's got a 208 I think.<br>
<br>
